name: tRNA nucleotidyltransferase
reaction: tRNAn+1 + phosphate = tRNAn + a nucleoside diphosphate [RN:R07285]
comment: Brings about the final exonucleolytic trimming of the 3'-terminus of tRNA precursors in Escherichia coli by a phosphorolysis, producing a mature 3'-terminus on tRNA and nucleoside diphosphate. Not identical with EC 2.7.7.8 polyribonucleotide nucleotidyltransferase.

references.title: 3' processing of tRNA precursors in ribonuclease-deficient Escherichia coli. Development and characterization of an in vitro processing system and evidence for a phosphate requirement.
RNase PH: an Escherichia coli phosphate-dependent nuclease distinct from polynucleotide phosphorylase.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 85 (1988) 4710-4.
